<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Abandon Old Housing Distribution System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The State Council has issued a
circular ordering all localities to stop the decades-old practice
of distributing public-owned apartments at very low rents to those
working in government departments and state-owned institutions and
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Beginning in the second half of this year, these employees will
have to purchase residences with either their own salaries, public
housing funds, mortgage loans, or, in some places, subsidiaries
from the government using apartment-building funds.
</P>
<P>
The exact time for implementation of the new housing system
will be set by local governments in accordance with local
situations, and the reform will be carried out step by step, the
circular says.
</P>
<P>
In principle, newly-built apartments will be available only for
purchase, not for rent, but local governments and institutions
will also provide low-income families with low-rent apartments for
leasing, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The country will continue to popularize and constantly improve
the public housing fund system, according to the document.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
