<HEADLINE> 77,881 HIV Positive Cases in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 77,881 HIV positive
and 6,059 AIDS cases have been reported in India up to June 30
this year, Indian Minister for Health and Family Welfare Dalit
Ezhilmalai said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to Lok Sabha, the Lower House of Parliament,
he said that the World Health Organization (WHO) said in a recent
report that about four million people are living with HIV
infection in the country.
</P>
<P>
An in-depth analysis of 5,014 AIDS cases showed that 199 cases,
or 3.89 percent, are reported to be under the age of 15, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
The government has imposed a ban on collection of blood from
professional donors with effect from January 1 this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
