<HEADLINE> Chirac's Support Rate Soars After World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac's
support rate has soared in the wake of France's victory in the
World Cup football tournament, according to a latest poll
published Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chirac's support rate now stands at 67 percent, seven points
more than last month, and that of Prime Minister Lionel Jospin now
stays at 65 percent, two points higher, said the poll conducted by
the BVA-Paris Match among 1,005 people from July 16 to 18.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for Chirac to win more support than
Jospin since they began government cohabitation 13 months ago.
</P>
<P>
Chirac has won more support from the partisan fields of the
Green Party, the Socialist Party and his Gaullist RPR.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-seven percent of the people polled said that Chirac is
"very good" or "fairly good" as president, against 23 percent who
said the opposite.
</P>
<P>
The poll also shows that more French people now consider the
political cohabitation between the right and the left is a good
thing than before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
