<HEADLINE> Torrential Rains Hit Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Torrential storms lasting from 5:00
am to 4:00 pm today brought rainfall of 280 to 438 mm to Wuhan
City, capital of central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 40,000 people have taken up a vigil on the city's
400 km-long dikes along the Yangtze River to prepare for the
coming floods, according to local official sources.
</P>
<P>
Public traffic and power-supplies were brought to a halt in
many parts of the city, and so far 23 department stores and shops
have been flooded.
</P>
<P>
Rain and new flooding in the neighboring Poyang Lake area has
caused the waters of the Yangtze to rise.
</P>
<P>
By 8:00 pm, the water level at the Wuhan Pass Measuring Station
reached 27.53 m, 0.16 m higher than the day before yesterday and
0.23 m higher than emergency level, with a flow rate of 62,100
cubic meters per second.  
</P>
</TEXT>
