<HEADLINE> Palestinian Legislators' Delegation Leave for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Palestinian
Legislative Council (PLC) left for Washington Tuesday to discuss
with U.S. Congress members issues concerning the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
PLC Speaker Abu Ala, who is the head of the delegation, told
the Voice of Palestinian before departure that the visit is
important because this is the first PLC delegation visiting
Washington since the PLC coming into being in 1996.
</P>
<P>
"In reality, we look at the visit as important and I believe,
if God will be with us and the results are successive, the visit
will help improve the Palestine-U.S. relations," the Speaker said.
</P>
<P>
