strong and biased relation with Israel. We hope to establish a
relationship with the U.S. Congress which will gradually develop
so that its members will turn to understand more about our people,
society, problems and our people's sufferings," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said he will use this opportunity to tell the Congressmen
about the true picture of the Middle East peace process, about the
Palestinian positions in the peace talks with Israel and help them
have a more clear understanding about the Palestinian issue.
</P>
<P>
U.S. House Speaker Newt Gingrich visited Ramallah in May this
year and met with Abu Ala there.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two speakers promised to further
promote the relations between the lawmakers of the two sides and
Gingrich invited his Palestinian counterpart to visit
Washington. 
