<HEADLINE> Angola in Need of 0.47 Million Tons of Food in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUNDA, July 21 (Xinhua)-- Angola needs 470,000 tons of grain
the 1998-99 agricultureal year to deal with the food crisis
facing the country.
</P>
<P>
A report made jointly by the U.N. Agriculture and Food
Organization and World Food Program said that due to the abundant
of rainfalls, Angola will yield 594,000 tons of grain this year,
an increase of 38 percent over the previous year. But due to poor
infranstructure and transportation, much grain was stranded in
some grain-producing areas, especially in the central highllands
where have been seen as Angola's "grain Barn", and couldn't reach
the areas where food is badly needed, the report added.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the report said, though Angola's food production
will incrase this year, the country still needs 120,000 tons of
food aid from the international community during the 1998-99
agricultural year. Of the 120,000 tons of food aid, 90,000 tons are
in emergency.
</P>
<P>
If the world food aid can'nt reach Angola in time, 750,000
Angolans will face serious food crisis this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
