<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Expressing regret over the border
conflict between Yemen and Saudi Arabia, Jordan Tuesday urged the
sides to exercise restraint to avoid escalating the tension.
</P>
<P>
The problems between Yemen and Saudi Arabia should be solved
through "dialog and understanding" instead of the use of military
force, Information Minister Abdullah Ensour said after a regular
Cabinet session.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet decided to entrust Foreign Minister Jawad Anani
with the task of holding contacts with the concerned parties to
monitor the developments in the border conflict, Anani added.
</P>
<P>
Yemen's President Ali Abdullah Saleh Monday accused Saudi naval
ships of shelling its Red Sea island Duwaima, in which three
Yemeni guards were killed and nine others wounded.
</P>
<P>
The conflict on the Duwaima island, off the coastal area
marking the Yemeni-Saudi Arabian border, was only the latest in a
series of territorial disputes between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia and Yemen have been locked in border disputes since
1934. The tension was eased in 1995 when Sanaa and Riyadh signed a
Memorandum of Understanding in which they agreed to conduct
negotiations to solve the border demarcation. 
</P>
