<HEADLINE> Security Council Decides to Extend UNPREDEP Mandate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of the
United Nations Tuesday decided to extend the mandate of the United
Nations Preventive Deployment Force (UNPREDEP) in Macedonia for a
further period of six months until February 28, 1999.
</P>
<P>
In its resolution unanimously adopted, the Security Council
reaffirmed its commitment to the independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity of the former Yugoslav Republic of
Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
The council authorized an increase in the troop strength of the
UNPREDEP up to 1,050 to deter threats and prevent clashes, to
monitor the border areas and to report on illicit arms flows and
other activities that are prohibited.
</P>
<P>
The UNPREDEP, set up in 1992, was aimed to prevent conflicts in
other areas of the former Yugoslavia from spreading over to
Macedonia. 
</P>
