<DOCNO> XIE19980722.0063 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Chairman At LIFFE Confirmed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Brian Williamson, chairman of
Gerrard Group plc, has been appointed the new chairman of the
London International Financial Futures and Options Exchange
(LIFFE).
</P>
<P>
The Board of the LIFFE confirmed the three-year appointment at
a meeting Tuesday. The appointment takes effect on 3 August.
</P>
<P>
It was also announced at a press conference that Daniel Hodson,
the LIFFE's chief executive since 1993, has decided to leave the
exchange.
</P>
<P>
The current deputy chief executive, John Foyle, will become
acting chief executive until a new appointment is made.
</P>
<P>
Williamson said of his appointment, "I believe that the
challenges faced by LIFFE, for example, the advent of electronic
trading and increased competition, are placing more and more
demands on the chairman. I am, therefore, giving up my
chairmanship of Gerrard Group."
</P>
<P>
The new chairman was confident that the challenges can be
successfully met and that the LIFFE can become more competitive
and can deliver a first-class product to the benefit of its
customers and members.
</P>
<P>
Williamson said, "The exchange must continue to play a full
part in maintaining and growing international business in the City
of London to ensure that it remains the pre-eminent international
financial center." 
</P>
</TEXT>
