<HEADLINE> New U.S. Aircraft Carrier to Be Put in Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A new U.S. aircraft carrier
will be put into service, the Navy said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton will preside over the official
activation on Saturday in Norfolk, Virginia, of the Harry Truman,
the 13th aircraft carrier, "the most formidable ship ever put to
sea," the Navy said.
</P>
<P>
The Truman is the eighth nuclear-powered Nimitz-class carrier,
with virtually unlimited range at more than 30 knots without
refueling for 20 years because of its twin nuclear reactors, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The truman's air wing includes nine or 10 squadrons that fly
the F-14 Tomcat, F/A-18 Hornet strike fighters, Ea-6b Prowler
electronic warfare aircraft and multirole SH-60b seahawk
helicopters.
</P>
<P>
The Truman will serve the United States for half a century,
the Navy said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
