<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Cape Verde's Regulatory Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday an interest-free credit of 9.0 million U.S. dollars
equivalent to support Cape Verde's Privatization and Regulatory
Capacity Building Project.
</P>
<P>
This project is made up of the accelerated privatization
program, which also retrains and redeploys state-owned enterprises
staff and creates communication campaign, the consolidated
regulatory framework, which involves setting up regulatory
agencies to cover the various sectors under the privatization
program and a project coordinating unit, set up in the Office of
the Vice Prime Minister, responsible for project implementations.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be provided through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessional
lending wing for developing countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
