<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eleven Injured in East China Tornado </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A tornado swept through the eastern
suburbs of the port city of Ningbo in east China's Zhejiang
Province Tuesday afternoon injuring 11 people, five of them
seriously.
</P>
<P>
The twister lasted only five minutes and was confined to an
area of two to three square kilometers. However, it took the roofs
off more than 250 workshops, warehouses and residences, casting
many of them as far as 20 to 30 meters.
</P>
<P>
The direct economic losses caused by the tornado are estimated
at one million yuan (120,000 US dollars), said Chen Youli, deputy
director of the Ningbo Weather Meteorological Observatory.
</P>
<P>
The meteorologist said the tornado was caused by cold air
penetrating into Ningbo area, which has been under a system of
consecutive high temperatures and low pressure. The observatory
warned local residents of the impending tornado, though it could
not forecast the exact spot it would touch down, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
