<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Assassination of UN Observers in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Ministry's spokesman
Mahmoud Mohammadi on Wednesday condemned the assassination of
U.N. observers in Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Three U.N. observers along with their interpreter on duty were
ambushed and killed by unknown gunmen in Tajikistan Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Calling the killing as an "inhuman act," Mohammadi offered
condolences to the U.N., the families of the victims as well as
their nations, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said Iran believed that such atrocities were
orchestrated by opponents of peace and tranquillity in
Tajikistan. He emphasized the need for prompt implementation of
the Tajik peace accord. 
</P>
</TEXT>
