<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swaziland to Beef up Water Conservation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland is preparing a
water bill which will declare all water in the country an
economic national resource, a senior Swazi official said in
Mbabane Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The increasing scarcity of water demanded that the government
take measures to ensure water conservation, Swazi National
Resources and Energy Minister Prince Sobandla said upon his
arrival from the official opening of the Friekoppies Dam in South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Sobandla said the water bill will also address water pricing
to bring it in line with the cost of making water available to
consumers.
</P>
<P>
The preparation of the bill follows concern expressed by the
Swaziland Water Corporation over the large number of bore holes
being sunk in rural areas by farmers and others to avoid paying
the high tariffs for piped water supplied by the authority.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
