<HEADLINE> Singapore Foreign Minister to Attend ASEAN Meetings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Minister for Foreign
Affairs and Law S. Jayakumar will attend the 31st ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting (AMM), the 5th ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF) and
the annual Post-Ministerial Conference (PMC) with ASEAN's Dialogue
Partners, to be held from July 24 to 29 in Manila, the
Philippines, a statement from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the 31st AMM to be held on July 24 and 25, the ASEAN Foreign
Ministers will review ASEAN's activities and external relations
over the past year, lay down policy guidelines for the coming
year, exchange views on the regional financial situation as well
as the preparation for the 6th ASEAN summit scheduled for December
1998 in Hanoi, Vietnam, and sign a Joint Declaration for a
Drug-Free ASEAN, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The 5th ARF Ministerial Meeting will be held on July 27 and
ministers are expected to exchange views on regional security
issues, to review reports on progress made at the various
ARF-related meetings, such as the International Group on
Confidence Building Measures and the International Meeting on
Disaster Relief, and consider recommendations on the future work
plan of the ARF, it said.
</P>
<P>
From July 28 to 29, the nine ASEAN countries will meet their
counterparts from the ten Dialogue Partner countries and they will
also hold separate discussions with each Dialogue Partner for
exchange of views on economic and political issues, the statement
said, adding Singapore will chair discussions with South Korea and
India.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, no information is available on sideline talks
between the participating ministers. 
