<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Pledges Support for Turkey's EU Entry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Prime Minister Jose Maria
Aznar pledged Wednesday that Spain supports Turkey's bid for full
membership of the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Aznar made the promise at a joint press conference here
following his one-hour-and-half meeting with his Turkish
counterpart Mesut Yilmaz.
</P>
<P>
"As both members of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, I
believe that Turkey and Spain will cooperate in the issues
concerning the EU," said Aznar, who arrived here Tuesday for a
two-day visit aimed at boosting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Yilmaz complained to his guest about the "wrong
and unacceptable" attitude adopted by the EU toward Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The Turkey-EU relations fell to the lowest level last December
when the EU leaders made a formal decision at the Luxembourg
summit to exclude Turkey from the EU enlargement process.
</P>
<P>
In angry reaction, Turkey swiftly decided to suspend its
political dialog with the EU to protest its unjust attitude toward
the Muslim-dominant nation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Yilmaz and Aznar signed a plan of joint action on
political, economic and cultural relations after their talks in
the building of the prime ministry.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz said that "there is no political problem existing
between our two friendly and allied countries", adding it was
necessary for the two sides to give full play to the potentials
of enhancing bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz announced that he and Aznar agreed to hold a meeting
every year, but he fell short of disclosing the fixed place and
date for the next meeting.
</P>
<P>
He added that Turkey and Spain would hold a meeting of the
Mixed Economic Council in Madrid, capital of Spain, in October to
discuss ways of expanding trade and economic relations.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources said the trade volume between the two
countries was 1.78 billion U.S. dollars in 1997 and is expected to
increase to 2 billion dollars this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
