<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and Russian foreign
ministers today jointly urged India and Pakistan to enter into the
Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty and the Nuclear
Non-proliferation Treaty unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and his Russian
counterpart Yevgeny Maksimovich Primakov discussed the recent
nuclear tests conducted by India and Pakistan during today's talks
and jointly reaffirmed their positions not to recognize India and
Pakistan as nuclear powers.
</P>
<P>
It is important for China and Russia, both influential
countries and permanent members of the UN Security Council, to
conduct close consultation and coordination on issues concerning
regional and world peace and security, they agreed.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers covered both bilateral relations and
regional and international issues of common concern, reaching
consensus on a broad scale. They also noted that Sino-Russian
relations have maintained the momentum for sound development this
year.
</P>
<P>
They discussed in detail the arrangements for President Jiang
Zemin's coming visit to Moscow this fall and his scheduled
informal talks with President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Both agreed that the summit will be a great event in bilateral
relations and will undoubtedly further accelerate the strategic
cooperative partnership between the two countries, and they pledged
to make all preparations necessary to guarantee a successful
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Tang noted that the long-term and stable growth of
Sino-Russian relations is very important not only to the two
countries, but also to the entire region and the world. The
Chinese government will work hard to further advance a bilateral
relationship featuring equality, mutual trust,
good-neighborliness, mutually beneficial cooperation, and common
development into the 21st century, he added.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers met with the press following their
talks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
