<HEADLINE> Increased Foreign Trade In Southern Chinese Bonded Zones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shatoujiao and Futian bonded
zones in the city of Shenzhen in China's Guangdong Province did
more than 1.4 billion U.S. dollars worth of foreign trade during
the first half of the year, a 129 percent rise from the same 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
This means that the two were responsible for 7.1 percent of
Shenzhen's foreign trade, a big rise from the 3.2 percent of the
past.
</P>
<P>
A large amount of the zones' foreign trade was done by solely
foreign-owned enterprises, a 163 percent rise from the same 1997
period.
</P>
<P>
During the six-month period, 78.9 percent of their foreign
trade, or nearly 1.14 billion U.S. dollars, involved machinery and
electronics products, nearly five times the amount for the same
1997 period.  
