<HEADLINE> People In South China Region Asked To Report Corruption Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Procurator's offices in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region have dealt with at least
11,000 cases of corruption in the past decade, will the help of
75,000 tips from local people.
</P>
<P>
Local procurator's offices have been encouraging people to
provide tips and to increase their awareness of the need to
reporting corruption instances. Of these cases, 78 percent were
based on tips offered by local people, most of them involving
embezzlement, bribery, and appropriation of public funds.
</P>
<P>
A reporting center was established to deal with the tips and to
evaluate major cases immediately after receiving reports. Cases
with a great social impact are publicized as soon as they are
dealt with.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, special attention has been paid to protecting
informers and to providing proper credit or rewards. Reward funds
set up in 32 procurator's offices at the prefectural level have
offered more than 150,000 yuan (18,000 U.S. dollars) in rewards to
275 people credited with providing valuable clues in major cases.
 
</P>
