<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Chinese Needles Sew up Broken Legs in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
( by Chen Cailin )
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Having been declared by many
to be destined to stay in bed for the rest of her life, Belaynesh
Kilil, could hardly believe herself that with needles she regards
as almost the same as the sewing needles she uses at home,
Chinese doctors have helped her to stand up again.
</P>
<P>
A middle-age Ethiopian lady, Kilil was injured by car accident
and paralyzed in bed two and a half years ago.
</P>
<P>
She has been treated with western medicine in Addis Ababa for
one year and half, with no improvement.
</P>
<P>
It was all by chance, a friend told her that Chinese
acupuncture treatment would be effective for her disease.
</P>
<P>
Desperate for standing up again, she asked her relatives to
take her to Adama Hospital for Chinese acupuncture early this
year.
</P>
<P>
It was all magic for her, for after only 10-days of treatment,
her legs, which had been out of her control for nearly 900 days,
came back to herself -- she could move her two legs on bed.
</P>
<P>
And after two months, she could, with someone's help, stand
up.
</P>
<P>
Another 80 days later, she could walk alone with a walking
stick.
</P>
<P>
Chinese acupuncture, with a history of 2,000 years ago, is now
exerting its magical functions in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Assefa Teklu, Manager of Sodore Resort Hotel, is just as lucky
as Kilil.
</P>
<P>
Teklu suffered from lumbar muscle injury when he carried a
heavy thing uncautiously. Acute lumbar muscle injury gradually
became chronic. Then the strong Teklu had to rely on his walking
sticks to manage a few slow steps forward.
</P>
<P>
He consulted some specialists in many places for about half a
year, but no improvement was found.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, before he was ready to go to Europe to continue
his search for treatment his friend suggested him to go to see
Chinese acupuncturist in Adama Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Only 40 days of treatment by Chinese doctors in the hospital,
the manager recovered from his disease and went back to his work.
He can now drive his car to the hotel the same as he did before
the nightmare injury.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Gao Zhigang, an acupuncturist, was assigned to work in
Ethiopia by the Chinese government in August of 1996 as a member
of the ninth Chinese medical team.
</P>
<P>
According to the registered record, he has treated 13,000
patients who suffered from sciatica, lumbago, arthritis,
hemiplegia, etc.
</P>
<P>
He gave acupuncture treatment for about 30 patients daily
during his first days in Adama Hospital. As more and more
patients come to the hospital, his patients increased up to 60
patients a day.
</P>
<P>
Many patients came afar to Adama Hospital from different
regions of the country on Gao's reputation. Some even came from
the neighboring countries, as Eritrea, Somalia, Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
Many Patients with difficult and complicated cases have been
cured through Chinese acupuncture in the hospital.
</P>
<P>
Some who had been paralyzed find their standing-up stories go
like legends in their communities and the whole Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's governmental media, including Ethiopian News
Agency, state-run newspaper "Addis Zemen", Radio Ethiopia and
Ethiopian Television, vie with eath other to cover news of
Chinese acupuncture for curing paralyzed patients.
</P>
<P>
The media seem to have given wings to news of Chinese
Acupuncture wonders, so more and more patients are streaming to
the hospital.
</P>
<P>
The medical director of the hospital has to try his best to
expand the acupuncture room from one to two, and beds from three
to eight.
</P>
<P>
Currently, doctor Gao has been treating an average of 50
patients daily. Many more have to wait for two or three months
for their turns.
</P>
<P>
A student from Addis Ababa University told Xinhua that he came
from Shashaman Town, 250 kms away from Nazareth, because he had
facial palsy for two years.
</P>
<P>
He got satisfying results only for 10-days of needle
treatment, with his facial muscle back to function.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has one desire, that is, the Chinese
government can send more acupuncturists to Ethiopia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
