<HEADLINE> Heavy Rains Halt Traffic on National Highway in Hubei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rains swept through Huangmei
County in central China's Hubei Province from Tuesday evening to
early this morning and halted traffic on a 48-km section of the
National Highway 105.
</P>
<P>
The flooding, which was two meters deep in some areas, caused
one death, stranded 600,000 local residents and destroyed over
10,000 structures.
</P>
<P>
Local sources also reported that traffic along the National Highway
106 was halted in sections near Huangshi. Five people in Huangshi were
reported missing and over 3,000 urban residents were forced to
flee their homes.
</P>
<P>
Flooding has caused economic losses of over 250 million yuan in
the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
