<DOCNO> XIE19980722.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises Witness Double-Digit Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Township enterprises
recorded an incremental value of 1,016.3 billion yuan for the
first half of this year, up 14.3 percent on the previous year's
period, according to recent statistics from the Ministry of
Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents growth of 0.8 percentage points on May,
according to the ministry's Department of Township Enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Private businesses maintained rapid development with the growth
rate of 17.25 percent, or some 11 percentage points higher than
the figure for collective enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises also recorded a 5.5 percent rise in
exports to 272.5 billion yuan. The figure was 10.9 percentage
points lower than last year's same period, but 1.1 percentage
points higher than the May level.
</P>
<P>
The ministry pointed out that township enterprises continue to
face difficulties related to sluggish markets and falling
profits. The 92.4 percent sales/production ratio for township
enterprises during the period was 2.5 percentage points lower than
the national average.
</P>
<P>
Some 7.2 percent collective township enterprises sustained
losses, up 1.2 percentage points on 1997.
</P>
<P>
A ministry analysis of the overall operations of related
enterprises noted that the targeted growth rate of 18 percent will
be very difficult to achieve. It also pointed out time will be
required to realize the effectiveness of certain macroeconomic
policies designed to boost the economy, including increasing
investments and stimulating internal demand.
</P>
<P>
The ministry urged local governments to extend the greatest
possible efforts to help achieve the target set and suggested the
development of economy of scale and the introduction of
technological upgrades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
