<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Book Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Book Fair '98
opened here Wednesday, with over 350 publishers and book companies
from Hong Kong and beyond displaying their latest publications.
</P>
<P>
The book fair, entering its ninth year, was a long-awaited
festival for Hong Kong youths, who queued up early Wednesday
morning outside the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center for
 the fair's opening.
</P>
<P>
Apart from around 200 Hong Kong companies, there are exhibitors
from the Chinese mainland, Taiwan, Germany, the United Kingdom,
Singapore, Macao and Iran.
</P>
<P>
The organizer, the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC),
expected attendance to top last year's record of 350,000.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the book fair, TDC
Executive Director Michael Sze said, Hong Kong is an ideal center
for the production and publishing of Chinese and English language
books with its strategic position as the gateway to the Chinese
and neighboring markets, strong printing and publishing industry
and expertise in both languages.
</P>
<P>
With the freedom of publication, direct access to information
and advanced communications network, Hong Kong's publishing
industry has flourished over the years, Sze said. There are
currently over 200 publishing houses, 600 magazines and 54
newspapers in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The local printing industry, he added, is also renowned for
quality, quick delivery and competitive pricing.
</P>
<P>
The six-day event also featured a trade section, the
International Copyright Exchange, to further boost Hong Kong's
position as the copyright trading center in Asia.
</P>
<P>
In conjunction with the exchange, the Asian Publishing
Conference is to be held Thursday for the industry to exchange
views and explore cooperation opportunities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
