<HEADLINE> 50M Tree Seedlings Planted in Ethiopian Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 million tree
seedlings are being planted in the Tigre region of Ethiopia in a
bid to reduce soil erosion and meet the needs of construction.
</P>
<P>
The forestry development department of the region's
agriculture and natural resources bureau was quoted by
Wednesday's government newspaper, the Ethiopian Herald, as saying
that the seedlings are planted over 20 thousand hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
Forestry coverage rate in Ethiopia is only three percent. The
country loses 1.9 billion tons of soil to erosion every year.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the seedlings have been developed in
different nurseries run by associations and governmental and non-
governmental organizations. The number of nurseries in the Tigre
region alone has now grown to 694 from 31.
</P>
<P>
Over 280.4 million tree seedlings of different species have
been planted over an area of 750 thousand hectares of land in the
region since 1991.
</P>
<P>
Tigre region has six percent of the country's total
population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
