<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met
today with visiting Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Maksimovich
Primakov and reiterated that China's fixed policy is to develop
good-neighborly friendship with Russia based on long-term
stability and mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Russia is not only one of the world's most influential
countries, but is also China's largest neighbor, noted Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that his recent talks with Russian counterpart Sergie
Kiriyenko were highly effective and yielded fruitful results. "We
share the wish to further promote friendship and cooperative
relations between the two countries," according to Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Primakov expressed great pleasure in having the opportunity to
meet Zhu. He said Russia attaches importance to Sino-Russian
relations, and expressed hope for even stronger cooperation with
China in all fields.
</P>
<P>
He informed Zhu that Kiriyenko was deeply impressed during
their meeting, and reiterated that Russia is determined to
implement the agreement signed in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu and the visitor briefed each other on the economic and
financial situations in their respective countries, and exchanged
views on the financial turmoil affecting large parts of Asia.
</P>
<P>
Primakov expressed admiration for China's strong economic
strength in face of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
Vice Foreign Minister Zhang Deguang attended the meeting along
with Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Grigori Karasin.  
</P>
