<HEADLINE> Mozambique-Swaziland Border Closing Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The closing time for Namaacha
border station linking Mozambique and Swaziland will be prolonged
till 20:00 pm starting late August, three hours longer than the
current closing time.
</P>
<P>
The decision, made by the Mozambique-Swaziland joint committee
after their two-day meeting, is aimed at promoting border trade
between the two countries, the Noticias newspaper reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Namaacha station is a major station connecting the two
southern African countries, with a large number of goods and
people passing through it everyday.
</P>
<P>
The joint meeting, co-presided by Mozambican Foreign Minister
Leonardo Simao and his Swazi counterpart Albert Shabango, also
witnessed the signing of bilateral cooperation protocols on
banking, insurance, investment and trade.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between the two countries have been smooth, said
Simao, adding that more coordination is required for the patrol
of the common border, for criminals smuggling vehicles and
livestock often encroach on the border from two sides.
</P>
<P>
On the mal-treatment of Mozambican migrants illegally residing
in Swaziland, the joint committee agreed to solve the issue under
the existing system and institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
