<HEADLINE> Kinkel Calls for More International Efforts on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
urged the international community to make greater efforts to stop
the escalating Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued on Wednesday, Kinkel described the recent
escalation of armed conflict in Yugoslavia's Serbian province of
Kosovo as "extremely alarming."
</P>
<P>
"The danger that this conflict would spin out of control is
increasing," he warned.
</P>
<P>
Under current circumstances, the world community must
strengthen its peace efforts, Kinkel said.
</P>
<P>
The six-nation Contact Group, the European Union (EU) and the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) must
help find a way out of the impasse of violence and military
confrontation in Kosovo, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kinkel noted that EU countries were discussing the
possibility to play a "more visible role" in dealing with the
Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
"It is now necessary to act swiftly and effectively," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the statement, Kinkel also reiterated that there was no
alternative to a political solution to Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
The solution must be aimed firstly to arrange a status for
Kosovo to secure the interests and rights of all ethnic groups and
to preserve territorial integrity of Yugoslavia and other
countries in the region, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
