<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- In the conflict between the Islamist regime and the southern
 separatists, famine has been used as a weapon. The French
humanitarian organization Medecins sans Frontieres said that from
50,000 to 100,000 people have died of famine in Sudan since the
beginning of this year. The United Nations has also estimated that
 1.5 million people are faced with hunger in southern Sudan and
380,000 of them are in critical conditions.
</P>
<P>
-- A small number of Algerians demonstrated this week in a
number of European capitals trying to ask Europe help them refind
their family members whom they believed have been kidnapped by
military police in Algeria. Some international organizations
estimate that from 12,000 to 20,000 people have disappeared in
Algeria over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The brutal rising of the tension between Yugoslavia and
Albania after last weekend's fighting on their border is worrying
the international community. After the European Union appealed for
 an immediate ceasefire between the Albanian separatists in Kosovo
 and the Yugoslav army, the United States is searching for ``new
ideas'' to contribute to a solution to the Kovoso problem and to
lock the logic of an escalation in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
-- The risk of an aggravation of the Asian financial crisis is
troubling the United States, whose economic slowdown is greatly
attributed to the Asian crisis, said U.S. Federal Board Reserve
President Alan Greenspan on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
