<HEADLINE> Taiwanese Firms Investing More In Eastern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, July 22 (Xinhua)-- The port city of Ningbo in China's
Zhejiang Province has become a popular spot for Taiwanese
investment.
</P>
<P>
City authorities had approved more than 700 Taiwanese-funded
enterprises by the end of June, with 1.7 billion U.S. dollars
worth of contracts. One city official says he expects the
Taiwanese funds to continue for the next several years.
</P>
<P>
He said that, as the investment increased, the average
investment for each project also increased.
</P>
<P>
The 24 projects funded by Taiwanese companies that have 10
million U.S. dollars of investment each account for 82 percent of
Ningbo's total investment from Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
These companies are involved in petrochemicals, electronics,
textiles, building materials, machinery, agriculture, land
development, finance, information, and consulting, according to
the official. 
</P>
