<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- A new U.S. aircraft carrier will be put into
service, the Navy said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton will preside over the official
activation on Saturday in Norfolk, Virginia, of the Harry Truman,
the 13th aircraft carrier, "the most formidable ship ever put to
sea," the Navy said.
</P>
<P>
The Truman is the eighth nuclear-powered Nimitz-class carrier,
with virtually unlimited range at more than 30 knots without
refueling for 20 years because of its twin nuclear reactors, it
said. (US-Carrier)
