<HEADLINE> Visitor Arrivals Down in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- For the 12 months ending June
1998, New Zealand received about 1.46 million tourists, down 5
percent on the year ended June 1997, according to government
statistics released here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
There were 80,270 visitor arrivals last month, 4 percent fewer
than in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors from Asia totaled 18,600 in June this
year, a drop of 27 percent compared with that in June of the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, New Zealand residents left for 121,790 short trips
overseas during June 1998, up 11 percent on June 1997. In the year
ended June 1998, they took about 1.15 million short trips
overseas, up 3 percent over the previous 12 months. 
</P>
