<HEADLINE> 671 Kony Rebels Captured in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Uganda People's Defense Forces
(UPDF) have captured 671 rebels of Lord Resistance Army (LRA)
spearheaded by Joseph Kony in its recent incursion into Uganda
from Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The UPDF also killed 179 LRA rebels and recovered 180 rifles
during different clashes between April and June this year, the
army's information director Captain Shaban Bantariza was quoted
by Wednesday's New Vision daily as saying Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said: "Out of 671 captives, 300 were accomplished rebels.
Those are people who qualify to die without going home but they
are with us. The others were captives still going under
training."
</P>
<P>
These remarks were made in response to a statement by a ruling
party delegate at the national conference that the military
commanders in northern districts have abandoned war for private
business.
</P>
<P>
On July 15, 16 and 17, two rebels surrendered and two others
killed. Some 27 abductees were rescued.
</P>
<P>
On July 18, about 100 rebels of the Uganda National Salvage
Front II attacked a UPDF detachment at Medigo, West Nile. The
government army killed nine rebels and their leader Alidiga
Kelili.
</P>
<P>
"You can't abandon war for riches and at the same time get
these achievements," the army spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, President Yoweri Museveni told a press
conference that Kony lost some 600 rebels in clashes with the
UPDF over the last two months.
</P>
<P>
He said only when the rebels stop wrongdoing and confine
themselves to their base in southern Sudan can a real cease-fire
be possibly realized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
