<HEADLINE> Yingkou Zone Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Yingkou Economic and
Technological Development Zone in northeast China's Liaoning
Province approved 10 foreign-funded projects with investments of
over 10 million US dollars during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The projects, valued at over 234 million US dollars, were
mostly funded by American and European investors. The majority of
the projects involve industrial production in areas such as solar
energy equipment, zinc plates, new types of bricks and kitchen
equipment, with approximately half of the projects in operation.
</P>
<P>
The state-level development zone, established in 1988 in the
coastal city of Yingkou, has amassed well over eight billion yuan
in fixed assets investment, and has introduced 1.1 billion US
dollars in foreign investments from 22 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The zone plans to place priority on the use of funds from
Europe and America rather that Southeast Asia, and will extend
great effort to further improve the local investment environment.
</P>
