<HEADLINE> Taiwan-Financed Businesses In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
had approved 1,005 Taiwan-financed companies by this May, with 996
million U.S. dollars worth of investment.
</P>
<P>
About 600 million dollars of that came from Taiwan, according
to the provincial government's Taiwan Affairs Office. The
companies are mainly in the chemical, light industry, textiles,
power, pharmaceutical, and building materials sectors.
</P>
<P>
Henan has plenty of natural resources and an economy that is
complementary with Taiwan, whose investors first came here in 1988.
</P>
<P>
For the past several years, the government has had a policy of
encouraging overseas investment in central and western parts of
the country and an increasing number of Taiwan investors have
begun shifting investment from coastal areas to inland areas.
</P>
<P>
To attract more investors from Taiwan, the province has been
improving investment conditions and policies that protect the
rights and interests of investors.  
</P>
