<HEADLINE> Special Patient Cured in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese patient who could not
eat solid foods for 30 years has been cured at Zhongshan Hospital,
an affiliate of the Shanghai University of Medical Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The patient, whose last name is Yao and is 63 years
old, has been suffering from cardia spasm for three decades and
had to subsist on only liquid foods.
</P>
<P>
Yao was 1.65 meters tall and weighed only 35 kg weigh when he
came to the hospital for help, according to doctors.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Liang, an associate professor of thoracic cavity surgery,
removed the patient's narrow and scarred cardia with the help
of other doctors, and reconstructed the alimentary canal.
</P>
<P>
The operation was successful and the patient has recovered. He
can now eat normally and his weight has increased by several
kilograms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
