<HEADLINE> World Bank Grants Loan to Moldova </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank decided Tuesday
to grant Moldova a loan of 175 million U.S. dollars to boost its
reforms in social security, energy and agriculture sectors,
Moldova's state information agency, Moldpress, reported.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to carry out seven projects in the
former Soviet republic during 1999-2001, including the set-up and
improvement of the social investment and insurance systems, the
transformation of the public health, energy and agriculture
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The loan is aimed at helping the country fight poverty and
stabilize the economy growth, said World Bank representative James
Parks in the Moldovan capital Chisnau.
</P>
<P>
Moldova's foreign assistance usually comes from the World Bank
and the International Monetary Fund (IMF) which have given a total
of 540 million U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
