<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Closes ASC, SOM Meetings With Stress on Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) closed its two-day ASEAN Standing Committee (ASC)
meeting and Senior Officials Meeting (SOM) here Wednesday with a
pledge to build the ASEAN into a "community of the region's
peoples."
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN seeks to be a region unburdened by hunger, malnutrition
and poverty," said Domingo Siazon, secretary of foreign affairs of
the Philippines, which is this year's rotating chairman of ASEAN
annual meetings.
</P>
<P>
In his closing statement at the ASC meeting, Siazon noted that
there are greater challenges ahead that need to be faced. "But for
now, it is enough that ASEAN has inched closer as a community."
</P>
<P>
According to Siazon, the ASC meeting, also attended by the
ASEAN secretary-general and directors-general of the ASEAN
national secretariats, reviewed the work of the ASC in the past
year and approved the agenda of the ASEAN Ministerial Meeting
(AMM) to take place here later this week and a report on the ASC's
work to be presented to the AMM.
</P>
<P>
Siazon pointed out that Southeast Asia has changed in the past
year. "ASEAN member countries felt the painful crunch of the
financial crisis. Growth targets fell, unemployment indices rose
and our respective governments were hard-pressed to live up to
expectations."
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN, however, made efforts toward correcting this problem by
establishing monitoring mechanisms through the assistance of the
Asian Development Bank, prompting transparency and pursuing
national internal readjustments," he declared.
</P>
<P>
He added that the ASEAN is being transformed because over the
past 12 months, it is "moving closer toward building a community.
An ASEAN community."
</P>
<P>
He cited the adoption last December of the ASEAN Vision 2020,
which he said "will guide us into the next century." "It outlines
our goals and plans for uplifting the welfare of the peoples of
Southeast Asia and achieving the dream of a cohesive ASEAN
community."
</P>
<P>
In a bid to realize the ASEAN founding fathers' dream of
including all nations in the regional grouping, ASEAN admitted
Laos and Myanmar into its ranks in July last year. But the
membership of Cambodia was deferred owing to political turmoil in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Siazon said ASEAN members have extended their "full
cooperation" to the two new members in facilitating their
integration into ASEAN activities."
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN also expanded its cooperation in other areas such as
transboundary haze caused by fires in Indonesia, prevention of
forest fires in the region and eradication of transnational
crimes, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ASC and SOM meetings were held to make preparations for the
31st ASEAN Ministerial Meeting, which is scheduled to open here on
Friday and discuss questions including the financial crisis which
has been affecting the region since July last year, measures to
deal with the crisis and its effects, Cambodia, nuclear
proliferation in South Asia and transnational crimes and a
proposed shift in the ASEAN's policy from "non-intervention" in
member countries' internal affairs to "flexible engagement."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
