<HEADLINE> Storm Causes Big Damages to Washington Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Driving rain and high winds
downed trees, knocked out electricity to about 100,000 customers
and caused scores of traffic accidents in the Washington area
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
The outages also caused some traffic signals to stop working
and resulted in traffic backups in scattered areas.
</P>
<P>
Some cars were reported damaged at a dealership in Montgomery
County, where part of a roof collapsed. Trees fell on some houses
in the suburbs.
</P>
<P>
The National Weather Service said there were reports of funnel
clouds in Montgomery County and Fairfax County, Virginia, with a
possible small tornado near Gaithersburg, Maryland. 
</P>
