<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Man Faces Drug Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A Ghanaian man has been charged
with trying to smuggle two kilograms of heroin out of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Mohammed Awalabu, 26, was arrested at a post office in Pattaya,
a Thai coastal city, as he was about to post a parcel to Burkina
Faso in Africa. In it officials allegedly found the heroin, the
Bangkok Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Narcotics Suppression Division police said they had learned
that the suspect was a major drug dealer working for an
international ring.
</P>
<P>
The drug locally is worth 200,000 baht (5,000 U.S. dollars) per
kilogram but could fetch 10 times more abroad. 
</P>
