<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Media Keen on SAARC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lankan government
Information Department official Wednesday said the international
media were showing a keen interest in the upcoming summit of the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC).
</P>
<P>
Already over 150 foreign media personnel have applied for
accreditation to cover the event and more such applications were
expected, the official told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
All leaders of the seven countries of the SAARC will go to
Colombo and the interest in the Colombo SAARC summit, which is to
be held on July 29-31, had been further enhanced by the proposed
meeting of the prime ministers of India and Pakistan during the
summit, he said.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first top level meeting of the two countries
after the nuclear tests conducted by them in May this year.
</P>
<P>
The Colombo summit is expected to defuse tensions between the
two countries, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory work for the media sector to cover the summit
has been completed. A special media center will be operating
during the summit at the Ceylon Intercontinental Hotel. It will
have all facilities including transport, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
