<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Thai Travel
Agents (ATTA) has proposed that Thailand should have a reciprocal
cooperative agreement with China on tourism, according to ATTA
president Anant Sirisant.
</P>
<P>
Anant and Jurin Laksanavisit, minister of the Prime Minister's
Office, who is in charge of tourism promotion, will visit Kunming,
Yunnan province, later this month to negotiate with the Chinese
side on a cooperative tourism program, the Nation reported
Wednesday.
</P>
