<HEADLINE> Italy's Employment Rate to Rise 0.4 Percent in 1998-1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 21 (Xinhua) -- During the two-year period of
1998-1999, employment rate in Italy will increase by only 0.4
percent, predicted the Organization for Cooperation and Security
in Europe (OCSE) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In its 1998 Report on Employment Prospects, OCSE said that the
rise in employment in Italy will be lower than the average for the
industrialized nations that it put at 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
It said the number of unemployed in Italy would remain stable
at 2.7 million, 11.9 percent of the work force.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the report, Italian Labor Minister Tiziano Treu
said, "the data shows just how complex employment policies are"
and "the government must still do a lot more than it has so far."
</P>
<P>
The OCSE report added that, over the same two-year period,
Italy's GDP would grow by 2.5 percent, in line with other
industrialized nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
