<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Urges Argentina to Extradite Nazi War Criminal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia is urging Argentina to extradite the former Nazi war
criminal Dinko Ssakich's wife Nada Ssakich.
</P>
<P>
According to an official announcement, the judicial department
has accused Nada Ssakich of committing genocide and other war
crimes in the former Yugoslavia during World War II.
</P>
<P>
The Ssakichs have resided in Argentina for many years.
</P>
<P>
Ssakich was a commanding officer at the Jasenovac Nazi
concentration camp in the former Yugoslavia during World War
II. The judicial department claims that he butchered more than
70,000 Serbians, Jews, gypsies and Croatians.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia announced in 1947 that Dinko Ssakich was a war
criminal. Ssakich has already been tried for war crimes, but his
wife Nada Ssakich remains at large. 
</P>
</TEXT>
