<HEADLINE> Silt-Sample Display Room for Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A silt-sample display room has
been opened in the Jinjiang Hydrology Bureau on the
middle reaches of the Yangtze River in central China's Hubei
Province.
</P>
<P>
The silt sample room, the first of its kind on the Yangtze
River, has more than 5,000 silt samples on display. The samples
were collected from over a 2,000-kilometer stretch of the
river: from Pingshan on the upper reaches to Datong on the lower
reaches.
</P>
<P>
The samples show the composition, sources, and development
of Yangtze River silt, revealing characteristics
of the geology, hydrology, and topography of the river, according
to experts.
</P>
<P>
Many of these samples were collected by Zhou Fengqin, a senior
engineer at the Jinjiang Hydrology Bureau, whose plan was used to
establish the display room. River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
