<HEADLINE> Panama to Host 12th Group of Rio Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, July 21(Xinhua) -- Fourteen Latin American heads
of state will meet in Panama early next September to attend the
twelfth summit of the Group of Rio, announced Panamanian Foreign
Minister Ricardo Alberto Arias on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The summit, a regional political dialogue and coordination
mechanism, will celebrate the beginning of the handing over of the
Panama Canal, Arias said.
</P>
<P>
The summit will focus on the full incorporation of the group of
Central American countries and the Dominican Republic, Arias said.
</P>
<P>
The summit's Organizing Commission is headed by Ivette Franco,
ministerial cabinet chief of the Foreign Ministry. The commission
also includes 15 officials from other governmental institutions.
</P>
<P>
In view of the experience of the same personnel in organizing
the 26th general assembly of the Organization of American States
in 1996, the Summit of the Group of Rio, and the European Union in
1997, the Panama summit will surely be a success, thus enhancing
Panama's international standing, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Besides Panama, other countries of the Group of Rio are
Argentina, Brazil, Colombia, Mexico, Uruguay, Venezuela, Chile,
Ecuador, Bolivia, Peru, Paraguay, with El Salvador and Guyana
serving as representatives of the Central American and Caribbean
regions. 
</P>
