<HEADLINE> Czech's Unemployment Rate Hits Record High in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Czech Republic's unemployment
rate reached a monthly record of 13.5 percent by the end of June,
said official statistics here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
More than 375,000 people, 49.7 percent of whom female, were
out of jobs, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment situation in some central cities was among
the most serious, and in places like Revuca, unemployment rates
climbed to a high of 27 percent.
</P>
<P>
Czech's jobless rate is one of the highest in Europe. In
1997, it stood at 12.96 percent, and in the first six months of
this year, went up to above 13 percent except in May when it was
12.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say an unhealthy economic structure is among the main
forces dragging up the unemployment rate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
