<HEADLINE> Beijing's Great Hall Of The People Getting Facelift </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Great Hall of the People, one
of China's most important political and tourist sites, in the
center of Beijing on Tiananmen Square, is getting a facelift.
</P>
<P>
The renovation is one of dozens of projects Beijing began
recently in preparation for the 50th anniversary celebrations of
the People's Republic, scheduled for October 1 of next year.
</P>
<P>
The State Council, China's highest administrative body, has
decided to have the facing on 50,000 square meters of the
building's exterior replaced with granite from Fujian Province and
to have 11 large pillars rebuilt.
</P>
<P>
The glazed tile used to face parts of the hall will also be
changed.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hall of the People was built in 1959 and now receives
more than 10,000 visitors every day. 
</P>
