<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Tells Provinces To Be Prepared For Flooding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, who is
general secretary of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee, has told provinces and cities along the Yangtze River
to get prepared for possible flooding in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke by phone with Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao who is in
charge of the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan, the capital of Hubei Province, especially needs to get
ready, he said, because it has been hit by torrential rains over
the past few days and the river's second flood peak is expected to
hit the city on July 23.
</P>
<P>
The leader emphasized the importance of reinforcing dikes,
eliminating standing water in preparing for the coming floods. He
said that every effort should be made in this work and in
protecting lives and property.
</P>
<P>
Jiang extended his best wishes to the officials, local people,
People's Liberation Army soldiers, public security officers, and
armed police who are involved in the flood relief work and told
local Party committees and local governments to take good care of
people in flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
As a result of Jiang's phone call, the flood control
headquarters issued an emergency circular to provinces and
cities on making the dikes perfectly safe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
