<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Fixed-Assets Investment Reaches 51.2 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's largest trade and
financial city has invested 51.2 billion yuan (about six billion
U.S. dollars) in fixed assets in the first half of this year, a
drop of 8.1 percent from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's fixed assets investment has nosedived quickly since
the beginning of the year, but the city took immediate measures to
encourage more investments in this sector to secure a 10 percent
economic growth rate this year.
</P>
<P>
Fixed assets investments began rising in June and reached 12
billion yuan, up 14.3 percent from the May figure, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
The total investment in capital construction projects over the
past six months reached 24.4 billion yuan, higher than that of the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The investment in the Pudong New Area gained a 7.4 percent
growth in the first half of this year, topping 15.8 billion
yuan. And overseas cash flow into the city also leaped by 27.6
percent over the same period last year, reaching 11.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
However, the city's investment in technological upgrading over
the past few months dropped by 20 percent, and investment in real
estate development fell 8.2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
