<HEADLINE> Greene Wins Men's 100m Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ato Bolden of Trinidad and Tabago won the silver at 10.00 and
Brian Lewis of the United States snatched the bronze in 10.25.
</P>
<P>
World record holder Donovan Bailey of Canada was beaten into
seventh in 10.30.
</P>
<P>
The race didn't get start until the third gun, but Greene, who
clocked 9.86 to win the world title last year, had a perfect start
and surged ahead as a clear winner in his final strides.
</P>
<P>
Bolden, who trains with Greene and ran the fastest time of
9.86this year, looked strong in the first half. He and Greene
celebrated their victory after the race. 
</P>
