<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morceli Wins Men's Mile Title  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Noureddine Morceli of Algeria

successfully defended his title in the men's mile race with a time

of three minute 53.39 seconds in the athletics competition at the

Goodwill Games here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
William Tanui and Daniel Komen, both from Kenya, claimed the

silver and bronze medals, in 3:54.05 and 3:54.78 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Morceli, who kept a winning streak of 45 races in the mile and

1,500m from 1992 to 1996, lured second to Komen until the last

lap. Komen, who set the 3,000 and 5,000 meters world record in his

first two races this season, led the pace in style and looked very

strong.
</P>
<P>
But Morceli made his move at the bell with a fabulous kick,

opening a two-meter gap from chasing Komen and Tanui. The Algerian

kept his advantage till the victory, holding off the Kenyans' late

surge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
