<HEADLINE> Earthquake Re-hit Southern Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on the
Richter Scale hit Xatongmon County in the southern part of Tibet
at 22:40 Tuesday (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
According to the China Seismological Bureau, the epicenter was
located at 30.4 degrees north latitude and 87.5 east longitude.
</P>
<P>
It was the second strong earthquake that jolted the county in
the past couple of days. On July 20, the area was struck by an
earthquake measuring 6.1 on the Richter Scale.
</P>
<P>
No casualties have been reported yet.  
</P>
