<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Festina Coach Assumes Responsibility for Dope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Bruno Roussel, detained chief of
Festina who has been expelled from the Tour de France on doping
charges, said in Lille on Tuesday he took responsibility for his
team's behaviour and called for clearer laws on banned substances.
</P>
<P>
He said in a statement he had not seen or known everything
that was going on in his team, whose masseur was arrested earlier
this month on a charge of smuggling doping supplies.
</P>
<P>
"But it is incumbent on me as team director to assume
responsibility for everything, including that which I neither saw
nor knew about," he said.
</P>
<P>
"In view of what I am now experiencing and the criticism that
has been directed at me, that we must have clear rules and that
everyone at every level makes sure they are respected."
</P>
<P>
Roussel, now being held for questioning in Lille, asked in his
statement whether "we have the right to demand athletes to give
performances that go beyond the limits of a cyclist's capacities".
</P>
<P>
Festina riders, now out of the tour, could be called before an
investigating judge before the end of the week, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
