<HEADLINE> Massi Wins 10th Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Veteran Rodolfo Massi beat fellow
Italian Marco Pantani to win the first mountain stage of the Tour
de France from Pau to Luchon on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Jan Ullrich of Germany was also in
excellent form over the five major passes, trailing Massi by 59
seconds to finish eighth, but recapturing the leader's yellow
jersey, two days after losing it to Frenchman Laurent Desbiens.
</P>
<P>
Massi, who led the race from the first pass in the 196.5-km
10th stage, won in just under six hours, 36 seconds ahead of
Pantani.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Ullich leads American Bobby Julich on the
overall standings by one minute 18 seconds and Dane Bo Hamburger
by 2:17. 
</P>
