<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Colombian drug-dealers Jose
Delaguia Pua and Nelson Cuelo Galdino were arrested Tuesday with
12 kilograms of heroin by federal police in Rio Solimoes, 1,105
kilometers from Manaus, capital of the state of Amazonas.
</P>
<P>
Amazonas Police Superintendents Claudio Rosa told reporters the
two Colombian drug traffickers, residing at Leticia, Colombia,
were apprehended red-handed in Fraganti by the federal police.
</P>
