<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's international
Roberto Carlos said here on Tuesday that only their team doctor
Lidio knew what happened to his teammate and super star Ronaldo
in Brazil's loss to France in the World Cup final on July 12.
</P>
<P>
"One day doctor Lidio (Toledo) is going to reveal what really
happened to Ronaldo," Roberto Carlos told the local press.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Carlos was Ronaldo's room mate when he suffered a 30
to 40 second convulsion before the World Cup final.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know the name of what Ronaldo had. All I know is that
it was serious, very serious," Carlos said.
</P>
<P>
Carlos added that they were chatting in the hotel room before
the final when Ronaldo stopped talking, went pale and started to
sweat heavily.
</P>
<P>
As the convulsions started, his arms went crooked and his
hands looked deformed because of nervous tension. Other players
say he foamed at the mouth and swallowed his tongue. 
