<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Melinte Beats Women's Hammer World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Mihaela Melinte of Romania beat
the women's hammer world record with an awesome toss of 72.64
meters at the Goodwill Games here today.
</P>
<P>
The previous listed record was 69.46 meters. Olga Kuzenkova
of Russia also surpassed the old record with a 70.98 throw,
followed by Amy Palmer of the United States, at 66.33.
</P>
<P>
Kuzenkova had beaten the 69.46 mark with a brilliant toss of
73.80 meters on May 15 in Tolyatti, Russia, but her result has not
been sanctioned by the International Amateur Athletics Federation
as a new world record.
</P>
<P>
Melinte opened with a 67.35m effort, but Kuzenkova showed she
was in a good shape, hitting 70.73 meters immediately after the
Romanian.
</P>
<P>
After Melinte registered her winner, the Russian looked
nervous and lost her confidence. She fouled in the second round,
and produced her longest toss of the day in her next outing.
</P>
</TEXT>
